斯塔斯登","lifeSummary":"当Alice Middleton于大约1279年出生在英国貝德福爾伍頓时，她的父亲Roger Middleton29岁，母亲Sara25岁。她于1300年与Alexander Bozum II在英国貝德福爾朗斯頓结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。"},"hr":{"about 1279–":"oko 1279.–preminula","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–preminula","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300.–1390","1252–Male":"1252–preminuo","1256–1320":"1256–1320","1330":"1330","1252":"1252","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300.","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1320":"1320","about 1279":"oko 1279.","about 1277":"oko 1277.","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wootton, Bedfordshire, England":"Wootton, Bedfordshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England":"Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England"},"cs":{"about 1279–":"okolo 1279–Zesnulá","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–Zesnulá","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1252–Male":"1252–Zesnulý","1256–1320":"1256–1320","1330":"1330","1252":"1252","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1320":"1320","about 1279":"okolo 1279","about 1277":"okolo 1277","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wootton, Bedfordshire, England":"Wootton, Bedfordshire, Anglie","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, Anglie","Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England":"Stagsden, Bedfordshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1279–":"omkring 1279–Afdød","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–Afdød","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1252–Male":"1252–Afdød","1256–1320":"1256–1320","1330":"1330","1252":"1252","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1320":"1320","about 1279":"omkring 1279","about 1277":"omkring 1277","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wootton, Bedfordshire, England":"Wootton, Bedfordshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England":"Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1279–":"circa 1279–Overleden","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–Overleden","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1252–Male":"1252–Overleden","1256–1320":"1256–1320","1330":"1330","1252":"1252","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1320":"1320","about 1279":"circa 1279","about 1277":"circa 1277","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wootton, Bedfordshire, England":"Wootton, Bedfordshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England":"Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England"},"en":{"about 1279–":"about 1279–Deceased","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–Deceased","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1252–Male":"1252–Deceased","1256–1320":"1256–1320","1330":"1330","1252":"1252","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1320":"1320","about 1279":"about 1279","about 1277":"about 1277","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wootton, Bedfordshire, England":"Wootton, Bedfordshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England":"Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Middleton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the places so called. In over thirty instances from many different areas, the name is from Old English <i>midel</i> ‘middle’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’. However, Middleton on the Hill near Leominster in Herefordshire appears in Domesday Book as <i>Miceltune</i>, the first element clearly being Old English <i>micel</i> ‘large’, ‘great’ (see   Middlebrook  ). Middleton Baggot and Middleton Priors in Shropshire have early spellings that suggest <i>gem̄thhyll</i> (from <i>gem̄th</i> ‘confluence’ + <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’) + <i>tūn</i> as the origin. This surname is also found in Scotland and Ireland.","History: A Scottish family of this name derives it from lands at Middleto(u)n near Kincardine. The Scottish physician Peter Middleton practiced in New York City after 1752 and was one of the founders of the medical school at King's College (now Columbia University) in 1767. One of the earliest of the Charleston, SC, Middleton family of prominent legislators was Arthur Middleton, born in Charleston in 1681. The name has also been established in Ireland since at least the 13th century; its presence was reinforced by settlers in the 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Midthun","meanings":["Norwegian: habitational name from any of about ten farmsteads in western Norway named Midtun, from Old Norse <i>mith</i> ‘middle’ + <i>tún</i> ‘enclosure, farmstead’. Compare   Middleton  ."]},{"name":"Melton","meanings":["English (northern): habitational name from any of various places, for example in Leicestershire, Lincolnshire, Norfolk, and Yorkshire, all of which have the same origin as   Middleton  , with Old English <i>middel</i> replaced by its Old Norse equivalent <i>methal</i> after the Scandinavian settlement of northern and eastern England."]},{"name":"Middlebrook","meanings":["English: habitational name from a lost <i>Micklebrook</i> in Blackburn (Lancashire), recorded as <i>Mikelbroc</i> in the 13th century. The placename appears to derive from Old English <i>micel</i> ‘big’ + <i>brōc</i> ‘brook, stream’. The surname has undergone a dissimilatory or folk-etymological change from <i>Mickle-</i> to <i>Middle-</i>."]},{"name":"Milton","meanings":["English and Scottish: habitational name from one or other of the many places called Milton, or sometimes Middleton (see   Middleton  ) and occasionally Melton (see   Melton  ), most of which derive from Old English <i>middel</i> ‘middle’ or <i>myln</i> ‘mill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":11,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":36,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":49,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":103,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Middleton was born about 1279, in Wootton, Bedfordshire, England, her father, Roger Middleton, was 29 and her mother, Sara, was 25. She married Alexander Bozum II in 1300, in Roxton, Bedfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1279–":"umbes 1279–Surnud","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1252–Male":"1252–Surnud","1256–1320":"1256–1320","1330":"1330","1252":"1252","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1320":"1320","about 1279":"umbes 1279","about 1277":"umbes 1277","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wootton, Bedfordshire, England":"Wootton, Bedfordshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England":"Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1279–":"noin 1279–Kuollut","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1252–Male":"1252–Kuollut","1256–1320":"1256–1320","1330":"1330","1252":"1252","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1279":"1279","1300":"1300","1256":"1256","1277":"1277","1320":"1320","about 1279":"noin 1279","about 1277":"noin 1277","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Wootton, Bedfordshire, England":"Wootton, Bedfordshire, England","Roxton, Bedfordshire, England":"Roxton, Bedfordshire, England","Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England":"Stagsden, Bedfordshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1279–":"environ 1279–Décédée","1277–1320":"1277–1320","1279–Female":"1279–Décédée","1274–1330":"1274–1330","1300–1390":"1300–1390","1252–